  "overview": "A new high end residential development located in the district of Qiantan, Pudong near the centre of Shanghai. Located adjacent to generous riverside parklands, comprehensive sports facilities and the prestigious Wellington International School this is a highly desirable neighbourhood. \n\nThe project comprises 6 residential towers, ranging from eight to eleven stories. Dramatic glass sloped roof penthouses crown the eleven storey tower blocks, with simpler roofscapes to the shorter eight storey block buildings.  \n25 000 m2 of GFA is provided across 177 units with a variety of 2 bedroom, 3 bedroom, 3 bedroom plus study and duplex configurations. \nThe 6 buildings are sited to address the 4 street edges, creating a generous landscaped social heart to the site. \nAll units are minimum dual aspect, maximising views to the adjacent parkland and river, Southern daylight access and privacy. \n\nThe buildings feature a structural steel frame with composite deck flooring. Curtain wall cladding systems of glass, aluminium and dimensioned granite stone create a precise and restrained fa√ßade composition. Angular corner balconies hang from the primary structure offer prime promontories to the corner units and are celebrated in bright colour. Glazed and louvred balconies dress the other facades to allow full height operable glazing to all habitable rooms. The steel framed lift cores are expressed as separate towers with highly glazed link bridge connections.",
